name: concrete production, 30MPa, for drilled piles, with cement, Portland | concrete, 30MPa | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/26311/documentation

This dataset contains the production of concrete used for drilled piles with cement CEM I from primary aggregates (no input of recycled gravel or sand). This type of concrete is used in concrete pile construction under dry or wet conditions with high requirements (alkali-aggregate reaction (AAR), frost-dew resistance).;Density: 2400 kg/m3, content of cement: 355 kg/m3;Exposition class according to EN 206-1: no normative requirements

The activity starts with the ingredients for the concrete at the factory gate.

Includes the whole manufacturing processes to produce ready-mixed concrete, internal processes (transport, etc.) and infrastructure. No administration is included.
